    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="585"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d585">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 731.5.1/44.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">French Ambassador</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">French Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: The President of the Council
                    informs me that he has designated a plenipotentiary charged with the duty of
                    signing the contemplated protocol at Caracas. He will arrive there on January
                    20.</p>
                <p>Mr. Poinearé would be glad if your excellency would kindly have this information
                    given confidentially to the Venezuelan Government.</p>
                <p>I am at the same time directed to say to your excellency how sincerely my
                    Government appreciated the good offices you were so good as to extend to us
                    toward the solution which now appears to be at hand. Nothing would be more
                    acceptable to me than the discharge of such a duty with you.</p>
                <p>Be pleased [etc.].</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jusserand</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
